    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1620"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1620">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/130.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegrams of August 20 and 21. You will immediately inform the Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs that the Department of State has not acquiesced in the
                    proposition to substitute, as a security for the railway bonds, a portion of the
                    interest of the $6,000,000 referred to, and that no such proposition has been
                    presented to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
